headline: Grubhub waives delivery and service fees on restaurant orders over $50
summary: In a bold move to close the gap with rivals, Grubhub is waiving delivery and service fees on restaurant orders over $50.

headline: 2 S&P 500 Stocks on Our Watchlist and 1 We Avoid
summary: The S&P 500 (^GSPC) is often seen as a benchmark for strong businesses, but that doesn’t mean every stock is worth owning. Some companies face significant challenges, whether it’s stagnating growth, heavy debt, or disruptive new competitors.

headline: DoorDash Robot Dot And Senior Programs Raise New Investor Questions
summary: DoorDash (NasdaqGS:DASH) has introduced an autonomous delivery robot called Dot, aimed at handling orders in suburban areas where driver availability has been tight. The company is also supporting the bipartisan Delivering for Rural Seniors Act to expand food access for older adults, building on its existing Project DASH efforts.
